Cliffjumper looks back at Beachcomber. Beachcomber was calm and
collective as ussual, not letting anything he was thinking show.
CLiffjumper turned back. Their my kind of bots, thought Cliffjumper. We
need all the help we can get. Cliffjumper, resolved, grabbed upwards
towards Torca's hand, and shook it firmly. "I dont know of any other
groups, but I have a feeling something may happen. I say we find us a
place a baricade at, and start our own guerrilla warfare." Cliffjumper
suggested. Beachcomber folded his arms up, in agreement. He then
extended his hand, "I'm Beachcomber, welcome to the Autobots," He said,
looking up.
